{"type":"message","id":"2b12d6e2","parentId":"8780c177","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:38:45.843Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0e9vrdz2xyl7_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 093758\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze my current state and decide on the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nFrom the context:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending tasks include: TIC Experiment, defining significance scoring, tuning λ, etc.\r\n- Current focus is on COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n- Next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step is to begin the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment. I need to:\r\n\r\n1. Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n2. Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n3. Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n\r\nBut before I can do that, I should first create the experiment script or framework. Let me start by creating a script that:\r\n1. Reads the last N pulse logs\r\n2. Classifies content as invariant (recurring) vs variant (new)\r\n3. Tests prediction accuracy\r\n\r\nLet me create a TIC experiment script.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the next critical step for Phase 1 advancement. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariant vs variant content across recent pulse logs and test prediction accuracy.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate a new PowerShell script `scripts/run_tic_experiment.ps1` that implements the TIC classifier, analyzes the last 20 pulse logs, and produces metrics for invariant/variant classification and next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # TIC Experiment - Temporal Invariance Compression\r\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$PulseCount = 20,\r\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\r\n    [double]$InvarianceThreshold = 0.5\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$StartTime = Get-Date\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== TIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"PulseCount: $PulseCount\"\r\nWrite-Host \"InvarianceThreshold: $InvarianceThreshold\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Get pulse log files sorted by date (most recent first)\r\n$pulseLogs = Get-ChildItem -Path $LogDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | \r\n    Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | \r\n    Select-Object -First $PulseCount\r\n\r\nif ($pulseLogs.Count -lt 5) {\r\n    Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs, found $($pulseLogs.Count)\" -ForegroundColor Red\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Loading $($pulseLogs.Count) pulse logs...\"\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($log in $pulseLogs) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $log.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n        FileName = $log.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        WordCount = ($content -split '\\s+').Count\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Reverse to chronological order (oldest first)\r\n[array]::Reverse($pulses)\r\nWrite-Host \"Pulses loaded: $($pulses.Count) files\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 1: Extract candidate invariant phrases ---\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Step 1: Extracting Candidate Invariants ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n\r\n$allContent = $pulses | ForEach-Object { $_.Content } | Out-String\r\n\r\n# Pattern-based extraction (simplified - could be enhanced with NLP)\r\n$patterns = @(\r\n    \"Phase \\d+\",\r\n    \"\\[.*?\\]\",\r\n    \"Goal[s]?:\",\r\n    \"OBSERVATION|ACTION|MUTATION\",\r\n    \"\\.md\",\r\n    \"\\w+-\\w+-\\w+\"  # dates\r\n)\r\n\r\n$invariantCandidates = @{}\r\nforeach ($pattern in $patterns) {\r\n    $matches = [regex]::Matches($allContent, $pattern, [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)\r\n    foreach ($match in $matches) {\r\n        $phrase = $match.Value.ToLower()\r\n        if ($invariantCandidates.ContainsKey($phrase)) {\r\n            $invariantCandidates[$phrase]++\r\n        } else {\r\n            $invariantCandidates[$phrase] = 1\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# Select phrases appearing in >50% of pulses as true invariants\r\n$trueInvariants = @{}\r\nforeach ($candidate in $invariantCandidates.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n    if ($candidate.Value / $pulses.Count -ge $InvarianceThreshold) {\r\n        $trueInvariants[$candidate.Key] = $candidate.Value\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($trueInvariants.Count) true invariants (>=$([math]::Round($InvarianceThreshold*100))% occurrence)\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Top 5 invariants:\"\r\n$topInvariants = $trueInvariants.GetEnumerator() | Sort-Object Value -Descending | Select-Object -First 5\r\nforeach ($inv in $topInvariants) {\r\n    Write-Host \"  '$($inv.Key)' - $($inv.Value)/$($pulses.Count) pulses\"\r\n}\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# --- Step 2: Classify each pulse as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy ---\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Step 2: Classifying Pulses ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\n\r\n$classificationResults = @()\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    $content = $pulse.Content.ToLower()\r\n    $invariantCount = 0\r\n    $totalWords = $pulse.WordCount\r\n    \r\n    foreach ($inv in $trueInvariants.Keys) {\r\n        if ($content -match [regex]::Escape($inv)) {\r\n            $invariantCount++\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    $ratio = $invariantCount / [math]::Max($trueInv\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 09:38:34\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359525842}}
